re computation efficiency and overhead on ResNet-50 and ViT models.', 'Compare precision allocation strategies based on Hessian curvature vs. existing proxies (e.g., EMQ, SNIP) on ImageNet classification tasks.', 'Measure numerical stability (e.g., condition number, gradient variance) across different precision configurations.', 'Assess accuracy-efficiency trade-offs (e.g., FLOPs, memory footprint) for various bit-width configurations.', 'Conduct ablation studies to isolate the impact of curvature-aware diagnostics on model performance.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['Hessian computation may introduce overhead for very large models, although our method enforces strict bounds.', 'Theoretical guarantees rely on assumptions about Hessian smoothness, which may not hold for all architectures.', 'The method is limited to post-training quantization and does not address quantization-aware training scenarios.']}
