Based on the literature search results, I see that PAC-Bayes frameworks have been applied to spectral optimization in graph neural networks (GNNs), particularly in the context of sheaf-based models to address over-smoothing and provide stability guarantees. However, the application of PAC-Bayes spectral stability bounds to latency-aware inference systems remains underexplored. This gap presents an opportunity to propose a novel research direction that bridges PAC-Bayes theory with practical latency-aware inference systems.

### Refined Proposal

The refined proposal focuses on developing a **PAC-Bayes spectral stability framework for latency-aware inference systems**. The key idea is to leverage PAC-Bayes theory to derive spectral stability bounds that can be used to design and optimize inference systems with strict latency constraints. This approach will allow us to provide rigorous guarantees on the stability and performance of latency-aware inference systems, while minimizing computational overhead.

### IDEA JSON
```json
{
  "idea": {
    "Name": "pac_bayes_spectral_stability_latency",
    "Title": "PAC-Bayes Spectral Stability Bounds for Latency-Aware Inference Systems",
    "Short Hypothesis": "PAC-Bayes spectral stability bounds can be leveraged to design and optimize latency-aware inference systems with rigorous guarantees on stability and performance.",
    "Related Work": "Existing work on PAC-Bayes frameworks has primarily focused on spectral optimization in graph neural networks (Choi et al., 2025). However, the application of PAC-Bayes theory to latency-aware inference systems remains underexplored. Our proposal distinguishes itself by focusing on the intersection of PAC-Bayes theory and latency-aware inference, providing novel spectral stability bounds that are specifically tailored for inference systems with strict latency constraints.",
    "Abstract": "Latency-aware inference systems are critical for real-time applications, yet existing approaches often lack rigorous guarantees on stability and performance. In this paper, we propose a novel framework that leverages PAC-Bayes spectral stability bounds to design and optimize latency-aware inference systems. Our approach provides rigorous guarantees on the stability and performance of inference systems while minimizing computational overhead. We derive spectral stability bounds using PAC-Bayes theory and demonstrate their effectiveness through a series of experiments on benchmark datasets. Our results show that the proposed framework outperforms existing latency-aware inference systems in terms of both stability and performance, while providing rigorous guarantees that are crucial for real-time applications.",
    "Experiments": [
      {
        "Description": "Derive PAC-Bayes spectral stability bounds for a simple feedforward neural network.",
        "Metrics": "Stability radius, inference latency, accuracy"
      },
      {
        "Description": "Evaluate the effectiveness of the derived bounds on benchmark datasets (e.g., CIFAR-10, ImageNet).",
        "Metrics": "Stability radius, inference latency, accuracy"
