 layer-skipping and token-pruning methods (e.g., SAINT, QuantCache) in terms of latency, accuracy, and memory usage.', 'Analyze the spectral properties of the Jacobian matrix across layers and correlate them with the impact of layer-skipping on model performance.', 'Measure the perturbation introduced to hidden states when skipping layers using Frobenius norm and spectral radius metrics.', 'Validate the robustness of SGJLS under varying input distributions and domain shifts.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['The spectral analysis of the Jacobian matrix may introduce computational overhead during inference, potentially offsetting latency gains.', 'SGJLS relies on the assumption that spectral stability correlates with minimal perturbation of hidden states, which may not hold for all architectures.', 'The effectiveness of SGJLS may vary across tasks and datasets, requiring task-specific tuning.', 'Layer-skipping may introduce instability in models with highly interdependent layers, leading to degraded performance.']}
