- Compute the Hessian spectrum of hidden states across different layers and inputs. Evaluate the correlation between Hessian eigenvalues and quantization sensitivity.', 'Experiment 2: Precision Allocation - Implement a curvature-aware precision routing mechanism that maps Hessian spectral properties to precision tiers. Compare the performance against static and heuristic mixed-precision baselines.', 'Experiment 3: Numerical Stability - Measure the numerical stability of the proposed framework under varying precision tiers. Use condition number and relative error as evaluation metrics.', 'Experiment 4: Benchmark Evaluation - Validate the framework on single-GPU setups across diverse benchmarks (e.g., WILDS, CIFAR-10). Assess throughput, accuracy, and resource efficiency.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['The computational overhead of Hessian spectrum analysis may outweigh the benefits of precision routing.', 'The framework may not generalize well to architectures with highly non-convex optimization landscapes.', 'The deterministic nature of the precision allocation may limit adaptability to dynamic input distributions.']}
