putational overhead.', 'Experiment 3: Analyze the sensitivity of the Jacobian-based metric to different network architectures and layer depths. Metrics: Sensitivity score, latency reduction.', 'Experiment 4: Validate the framework in a real-time inference scenario (e.g., video processing). Metrics: Real-time latency, accuracy, computational overhead.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['Risk: The Jacobian-based sensitivity metric may introduce additional computational overhead, potentially offsetting latency gains. Mitigation: Optimize the metric computation to minimize overhead.', 'Risk: The approach may not generalize well to all network architectures or datasets. Mitigation: Conduct extensive empirical validation across diverse architectures and datasets.', 'Limitation: The framework relies on the assumption that layers with low Jacobian sensitivity are less critical for accuracy, which may not hold for all cases. Mitigation: Incorporate additional criteria (e.g., layer importance) to refine the skipping decision.']}
